@startuml
!theme plain
title Discord OAuth2 Callback Flow (Current)

actor Client
participant "Browser" as B
participant "Auth Service\n(Rust / Axum)" as Auth
participant "Redis\n(Ephemeral)" as Redis
participant "Postgres\n(Persistent)" as Postgres
participant "OAuth Provider\n(Discord)" as Provider

== OAuth Callback ==
Client -> B : Redirect from Discord with ?code & state
B -> Auth : GET /callback?code=xxx&state=yyy

== Step 1: Validate OAuth session ==
Auth -> Redis : Get OAuthSession {csrf_token, pkce_verifier, nonce} by session_id cookie
Auth -> Auth : Verify CSRF token matches state parameter

== Step 2: Exchange code for token ==
Auth -> Provider : POST /token with code + PKCE verifier
Provider -> Auth : Return access_token (and optional refresh_token)

== Step 3: Fetch user info ==
Auth -> Provider : GET /users/@me with access_token
Provider -> Auth : Return Discord user info

== Step 4: Upsert user and provider ==
Auth -> Postgres : Upsert User
Auth -> Postgres : Upsert UserProvider
Auth -> Postgres : Encrypt & store OAuthToken (refresh_token)

== Step 5: Create ephemeral session ==
Auth -> Redis : Store UserSession {session_id, user_id, role, session_version, expires_at=24h}

== Step 6: Cleanup OAuth session ==
Auth -> Redis : Delete OAuthSession

== Step 7: Set cookie + redirect ==
Auth -> B : Set "session_id" cookie (httpOnly, Secure, SameSite=Lax, max-age=24h)
Auth -> Client : Redirect to frontend URL

@enduml
